   "body" : "The code uses GetRandomBytes in several contexts where it's either unwieldy to return an error, or an error would mean a fatal exception anyhow. Bitcoin can't cope gracefully with a failing RNG. So just fail with an assertion error.\r\n\r\n@gmaxwell checked OpenSSL a while ago and discovered that it never actually fails, but it can't hurt to be a bit paranoid here.\r\n\r\n(somehow this gives me a deja-vu, I remember we did this before? can't find it in git history though)",
